radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix contains multiple appendicoliths and measures up to 9 mm in diameter with mild wall thickening. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Normal liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and adrenal glands. No evidence of focal lesions or hydronephrosis.
Showed a noncompressible tubular structure; however, this was not able to be traced back to the ileum and therefore was equivocal.
